      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Improve Kimi Code usage reporting",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nImproves Kimi Code usage reporting in CodexBar by aligning the Kimi provider with the upstream open-source Kimi Code implementation and `pi-provider-kimi-code`.\n\nMain changes:\n\n- Supports Kimi Code OAuth credentials from `~/.kimi-code/credentials/kimi-code.json`\n- Refreshes expired Kimi Code OAuth access tokens while preserving unknown CLI-owned credential fields\n- Keeps explicit Kimi API-key mode API-key only; OAuth credential fallback is limited to auto mode\n- Shows the active Kimi source:\n  - Kimi Code credential\n  - Kimi Code API key\n  - Kimi web cookie\n- Preserves Kimi quota windows from `limits[]` and shows Session before Weekly\n- Adds daily Kimi token usage from local usage records:\n  - Kimi Code `sessions/**/wire.jsonl`\n  - Pi session records for Kimi providers\n- Adds settings toggles for Kimi Code and Pi local usage sources\n- Estimates local Kimi usage cost with `pi-provider-kimi-code` pricing\n- Shows Kimi membership tier and fast mode as:\n  - `Tier: Allegretto`\n  - `Tier: Allegretto / Fast`\n\nThis keeps Kimi Code separate from Moonshot, Kimi K2, and generic Kimi API providers.\n\n## Upstream alignment\n\nThis PR follows the upstream Kimi Code implementation rather than inferring a separate protocol:\n\n- Kimi Code OAuth credential storage under `~/.kimi-code/credentials`: https://github.com/MoonshotAI/kimi-code/blob/3ea6ac278d2e57bb859ab423704bbd0fb2033c72/packages/oauth/src/storage.ts#L4-L6\n- Kimi Code token save path and permissions: https://github.com/MoonshotAI/kimi-code/blob/3ea6ac278d2e57bb859ab423704bbd0fb2033c72/packages/oauth/src/storage.ts#L90-L108\n- Kimi Code usage endpoint: https://github.com/MoonshotAI/kimi-code/blob/3ea6ac278d2e57bb859ab423704bbd0fb2033c72/packages/oauth/src/managed-usage.ts#L23-L39\n- Kimi Code `usage.record` writes a model field: https://github.com/MoonshotAI/kimi-code/blob/3ea6ac278d2e57bb859ab423704bbd0fb2033c72/packages/agent-core/src/agent/usage/index.ts#L26-L32\n- Kimi Code wire type requires `usage.record.model`: https://github.com/MoonshotAI/kimi-code/blob/3ea6ac278d2e57bb859ab423704bbd0fb2033c72/packages/agent-core/src/agent/records/types.ts#L68-L72\n\nThe same endpoint and OAuth behavior are also used by `pi-provider-kimi-code`:\n\n- Base URL and `KIMI_CODE_HOME`: https://github.com/Leechael/pi-provider-kimi-code/blob/89a5481f74d0b558a65d6bc0a71d923b266c2e7d/src/constants.ts#L38-L56\n- OAuth host/base URL environment handling: https://github.com/Leechael/pi-provider-kimi-code/blob/89a5481f74d0b558a65d6bc0a71d923b266c2e7d/src/constants.ts#L66-L75\n- OAuth refresh flow: https://github.com/Leechael/pi-provider-kimi-code/blob/89a5481f74d0b558a65d6bc0a71d923b266c2e7d/src/oauth.ts#L130-L169\n\n## Privacy\n\nLocal session scanning only aggregates usage records. It does not display raw prompts or session content.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh format`\n- `swift test --filter \"Kimi\" --skip-update`\n- `swift test --filter \"PiSessionCostScannerTests|ProviderSettingsDescriptorTests|Kimi\" --skip-update`\n- `swift test --filter \"fetcher merges native and pi codex history with normalized model names|fetcher merges native and pi claude history and ignores unsupported pi providers|fetcher maps Pi Kimi sessions into Kimi usage when Pi source is enabled\" --skip-update`\n- `make check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `./Scripts/compile_and_run.sh`\n",
        "branch": "kimi-code-oauth-credentials",
